headline: 3 Reasons LEN is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the last six months, Lennar’s shares have sunk to $119.99, producing a disappointing 8.3% loss - a stark contrast to the S&P 500’s 7.3% gain. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
